  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Spectrum has been acquired by GitHub and will be shutting down their service on August 10, 2021. They will now be supporting GitHub Discussions, but will not automatically transition user's existing Spectrum boards.\n\nThis works in our favor, as we wanted to reduce the number of support channels anyway. We'll need to message our deprecation plan and update our website links accordingly. We can take a \"soft\" approach by removing all links to Spectrum so no _new_ users onboard to the platform. Then, update our welcome message to coincide with Spectrum's own shutdown notice and direct people to Gitter, ZenDesk, and eventually Disqus.",
